On Apr 17, 2006, at 6:52 AM, Peter T. Owsianowski wrote:

> Went on the shakedown camping cruise this weekend and they squeal a  
> loud
> ringing squeak that is very loud.

To keep the brakes from squealing do the following:

- chamfer the pads at the edges
- make sure the backing plates are there with some anti-squeal  
between the pad and the plate
- the pistons must be locked into the 20 deg. position by the backing  
plates

